                Brampton is a suburban city in the Greater Toronto Area and is part of Peel Region. As of the 2011

                census, Brampton’s population is currently at 523,911. Brampton officially became recognized as a

                village in 1853 and gain city status as of 1974.
                <br /><br />
                The city was named after a city with the same name in Cumbria England. In Brampton, the area codes

                are either 905 or 289. The current nickname for Brampton is the “Flower City”.
